  "text": "The performance of a supply chain (responsiveness and sensitivity) is determined by decisions in the areas of inventory, transportation, facilities and information. Flexibility is an ability to change or respond to environmental uncertainty with little penalty in time, effort, cost and performance. In addition, competitive environment markets are becoming more international, dynamic, and customer-driven. Customers are demanding more variety, better quality and service, including both reliability and faster delivery. With increased global competition, buyers became more sophisticated, demanding more customization and shorter product life cycles. Firms are concentrated on the reduction of cycle time and solving the tradeoffs between efficiency and flexibility. It is also recognized the necessity of looking beyond the borders of their own firm to their suppliers to suppliers and customers to customers [CITATION_1] .",
